question: 栓抜き
sourceMnemonic: What do you use to <kanji>extract</kanji> a <kanji>cork</kanji>? A <vocabulary>corkscrew</vocabulary>! Or a <vocabulary>bottle opener</vocabulary> if you're feeling adventurous.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This word consists of the on'yomi reading for <ja>栓</ja> and the kun'yomi reading for <ja>抜</ja>, which you learned with <ja>抜く</ja>. If you can remember that, you'll be able to remember this too!
